Defendant Steven J Speer in court with attorney Jeremy J Guza.  Edward M Bremberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to counts 8 and 10 of the amended information. Counts 7 and 9 are dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

    The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE; as to each count

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
 *Attend a Parent Class

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 on each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: Ct. 8, 60 days huber, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.
